<item>
            <title>[JCR-1369] indexing-rules should allow wildcards for (global) property names</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-1369</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>eg:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;indexing-rule nodeType=&amp;quot;*&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;property&amp;gt;text&amp;lt;/property&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;lt;property&amp;gt;*Text&amp;lt;/property&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;lt;/indexing-rule&amp;gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
defines that all properties named &amp;#39;text&amp;#39; and all that end with &amp;#39;Text&amp;#39; should be fulltext indexed.&lt;br/&gt;
if the property name includes namespace prefixes, wildcards are only allowed for &amp;#39;any&amp;#39; namespace. eg:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
*:title&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
but not: j*:title&lt;br/&gt;
</description>
